<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1719,1894]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,339,1756,1782]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after Dr. V. Pešić in appreciation of his acarological work. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,320,1793,1819]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species belongs to a group of water species with a hyaline fork-shaped petiole. In all other species (
<taxonomicName box="[320,507,1831,1856]" class="Arachnida" family="Arrenuridae" genus="Arrenurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="forpicatoides">
<emphasis box="[320,507,1831,1856]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">A. forpicatoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Smit" authorityName="Smit" box="[523,731,1831,1857]" class="Arachnida" family="Arrenuridae" genus="Arrenurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perplexus">
<emphasis box="[523,669,1831,1856]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">A. perplexus</emphasis>
Smit
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Smit" authorityName="Smit" box="[789,1067,1831,1857]" class="Arachnida" family="Arrenuridae" genus="Arrenurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="queenslandicus">
<emphasis box="[789,1003,1831,1856]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">A. queenslandicus</emphasis>
Smit
</taxonomicName>
) the indentation of the cauda is narrow and deep.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
